<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="113" type="nomenclature">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="113">
<taxonomicName LSID="F9747AA2-1142-5E66-9992-A11B85ED9B2F" authority="Mongkolsamrit &amp; Noisripoom" authorityName="Mongkolsamrit &amp; Noisripoom" authorityYear="2022" class="Arachnida" family="Cordycipitaceae" genus="Parahevansia" higherTaxonomySource="treatment-meta" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Parahevansia" order="Hypocreales" pageId="0" pageNumber="113" rank="genus" status="gen. nov.">Parahevansia Mongkolsamrit &amp; Noisripoom</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel pageId="0" pageNumber="113">gen. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="113" type="type species">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="113">Type species.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="113">
<taxonomicName class="Arachnida" family="Cordycipitaceae" genus="Parahevansia" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Parahevansia koratensis" order="Hypocreales" pageId="0" pageNumber="113" rank="species" species="koratensis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="113">Parahevansia koratensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Hywel-Jones) Mongkolsamrit &amp; Noisripoom, comb. nov., Mycol. Res. 100: 1067 (1996).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="113" type="etymology">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="113">Etymology.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="113">
Morphologically resembling the genus 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Luangsa-ard, Hywel-Jones &amp; Spatafora, in Kepler, Luangsa-ard, Hywel-Jones, Quandt, Sung, Rehner, Aime, Henkel, Sanjuan, Zare, Chen, Li, Rossman, Spatafora, Shrestha, IMA Fungus 8: 348" authorityYear="2017" class="Arachnida" family="Cordycipitaceae" genus="Hevansia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Hevansia" order="Araneae" pageId="0" pageNumber="113" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="113">Hevansia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, but being phylogenetically distinct.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="113" type="description">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="113">Description.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="113">
Asexual morph: 
<taxonomicName class="Arachnida" genus="Synnemata" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Synnemata" order="Araneae" pageId="0" pageNumber="113" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="113">Synnemata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
arising from all parts of host, numerous, simple, brown at the sterile base becoming grey white with fertile part. 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="113">Conidiogenous cells</emphasis>
phialidic producing upper part of the synnemata. 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="113">Phialides</emphasis>
in a monolayer, single on basal lateral cells of synnemata, crowded, obovoid to ellipsoid with distinct necks. 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="113">Conidia</emphasis>
in chain, hyaline, smooth-walled, clavate.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="113" type="notes">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="113">Notes.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="113">
<taxonomicName class="Arachnida" family="Cordycipitaceae" genus="Parahevansia" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Parahevansia koratensis" order="Hypocreales" pageId="0" pageNumber="113" rank="species" species="koratensis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="113">Parahevansia koratensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, the type species of this genus, was originally described as species of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Lebert" authorityYear="1858" class="Sordariomycetes" family="Cordycipitaceae" genus="Akanthomyces" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Akanthomyces" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="113" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="113">Akanthomyces</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Hywel-Jones, 1996) and later transferred to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Luangsa-ard, Hywel-Jones &amp; Spatafora, in Kepler, Luangsa-ard, Hywel-Jones, Quandt, Sung, Rehner, Aime, Henkel, Sanjuan, Zare, Chen, Li, Rossman, Spatafora, Shrestha, IMA Fungus 8: 348" authorityYear="2017" class="Arachnida" family="Cordycipitaceae" genus="Hevansia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Hevansia" order="Araneae" pageId="0" pageNumber="113" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="113">Hevansia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.5598/imafungus.2017.08.02.08" author="Kepler, RM" journalOrPublisher="IMA Fungus" pageId="0" pageNumber="113" pagination="335 - 353" refId="B21" refString="Kepler, RM, Luangsa-ard, JJ, Hywel-Jones, NL, Quandt, CA, Sung, GH, Rehner, SA, Aime, MC, Henkel, TW, Sanjuan, T, Zare, R, Chen, M, Li, Z, Rossman, AY, Spatafora, JW, Shrestha, B, 2017. A phylogenetically-based nomenclature for Cordycipitaceae (Hypocreales). IMA Fungus 8 (2): 335 - 353, DOI: https://doi.org/10.5598/imafungus.2017.08.02.08" title="A phylogenetically-based nomenclature for Cordycipitaceae (Hypocreales)." url="https://doi.org/10.5598/imafungus.2017.08.02.08" volume="8" year="2017">Kepler et al. 2017</bibRefCitation>
). Our multi-gene phylogenetic analyses supported 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Mongkolsamrit &amp; Noisripoom" authorityYear="2022" class="Arachnida" family="Cordycipitaceae" genus="Parahevansia" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Parahevansia" order="Hypocreales" pageId="0" pageNumber="113" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="113">Parahevansia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as a monophyletic clade with strong support (MLB = 100 / BPP = 1.00, Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 1" captionStartId="F1" captionText="Figure 1. RAxML tree of Hevansia, Jenniferia, Parahevasia, Polystromomyces and related genera in the Cordycipitaceae from a combined ITS, LSU, tef 1, rpb 1 and rpb 2 dataset. Numbers at the major nodes represent Maximum Likelihood Bootstrap (MLB) and Bayesian Posterior Probabilities (BPP). Bold lines in the tree represent 100 % of MLB and 1.00 of BPP. Symbols on the right-hand side correspond to the types of ascospore morphologies found in each genus that are observed in natural specimens of Cordycipitaceae described in Fig. 2." figureDoi="10.3897/mycokeys.91.83091.figure1" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/719474" pageId="0" pageNumber="113">1</figureCitation>
). Therefore, we introduced 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Mongkolsamrit &amp; Noisripoom" authorityYear="2022" class="Arachnida" family="Cordycipitaceae" genus="Parahevansia" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Parahevansia" order="Hypocreales" pageId="0" pageNumber="113" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="113">Parahevansia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as a new genus that accommodates a single species, 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" genus="Pa." kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Pa. koratensis" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="113" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="koratensis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="113">Pa. koratensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
